68
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:54,041
- You're quite the hard worker,
aren't ya?

69
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:55,416
- I'm not done yet.

70
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,625
I still need to prepare dinner
and clean the rooms.

71
00:03:57,708 --> 00:04:00,125
I'll just take a quick break
then get back to work.

72
00:04:00,208 --> 00:04:02,208
- It's your first day
and you're so pumped up.

73
00:04:02,291 --> 00:04:04,375
- I'm only trying
to do my part.

74
00:04:05,125 --> 00:04:07,666
Besides, some important things
are at stake here.

75
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:13,833
By the way,

76
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:17,041
exactly what kind of magic
does Mili use, anyway?

77
00:04:17,125 --> 00:04:18,125
- Technically speaking,

78
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:19,500
Lia doesn't really use magic.

79
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:20,666
And for that matter,

80
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,083
her contract with me doesn't,
either.

81
00:04:22,166 --> 00:04:24,666
She's a spirit arts user.

82
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:26,041
- You mean magic users

83
00:04:26,125 --> 00:04:27,875
and spirit arts users
are different?

84
00:04:27,958 --> 00:04:30,291
- Magic users are able
to cast magic

85
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:31,541
by using their own mana.

86
00:04:31,625 --> 00:04:32,875
On the other hand,

87
00:04:32,958 --> 00:04:35,041
spirit arts users are able
to draw their power

88
00:04:35,125 --> 00:04:36,083
from mana in the atmosphere.

89
00:04:36,166 --> 00:04:37,125
- And just what makes those

90
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:38,666
two different,
Professor Puck?

91
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:41,333
- Basically, it depends on
whether or not you use a gate.

92
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:43,458
- A gate?
- Exactly.

93
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:46,000
Mana passes through a gate
that's within your body.

94
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:48,416
You draw mana in as well
as expel it out

95
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,291
through that gate.
[inhales sharply]

96
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:51,666
[exhales]
- I see.

97
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,666
So it's like a faucet for MP.

98
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,500
- You should have one,
too, Subaru.

99
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:56,708
- Whoa, really?

100
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:58,541
So you're saying that I can also
use magic, then?

101
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:01,666
- Want me to figure out what
your magical attribute is?

102
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:04,750
Magic users are divided
into four categories:

103
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:06,875
fire, water,
wind, and earth.

104
00:05:06,958 --> 00:05:09,125
[meowing]

105
00:05:09,208 --> 00:05:11,083
- That's a totally magic
sound effect!

106
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:13,083
- I now know what
your attribute is.

107
00:05:13,166 --> 00:05:14,791
- Yes, I can't wait for this!

108
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:16,541
<i>Is it the fire of passion</i>

109
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:18,458
<i>or a relaxed cool guy</i>
<i>water type?</i>

110
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:20,583
<i>A gentle wind flowing</i>
<i>across the plain,</i>

111
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:23,791
<i>or possibly the solid,</i>
<i>reliable earth?</i>

112
00:05:23,875 --> 00:05:24,916
<i>8- It's shadow.</i>

113
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,166
- Are you serious?

114
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:29,208
- Wow, you got shadow?
That's quite a rare one.

115
00:05:29,291 --> 00:05:30,791
- So what is shadow, anyway?

116
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:32,333
Must be a category error.

117
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:33,750
Weren't there only
four attributes?

118
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,625
- In addition
to the four basic ones,

119
00:05:35,708 --> 00:05:37,250
there are two bonus categories:
shadow and light.

120
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:40,125
- I bet it's something amazing.

121
00:05:40,208 --> 00:05:42,791
A talent that comes along once
in 5,000 years.

122
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:44,916
- With the shadow
magic attribute,

123
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,166
you can obstruct
an opponent's vision,

124
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:48,250
block sound,
slow down their movements,

125
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:50,458
and other things like that.

126
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:52,208
<i>- It's just debuffs?</i>

127
00:05:52,291 --> 00:05:54,000
- An easy one would be something
like Shamac.

128
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:55,916
- Of course.

129
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,333
That's a blinding spell,
isn't it?

130
00:05:57,416 --> 00:05:58,583
- [chuckles]

131
00:05:58,666 --> 00:05:59,958
Would you like me
to show you?

132
00:06:00,041 --> 00:06:01,166
- Wait, Puck.
Hold on a second.

133
