200
00:08:32,916 --> 00:08:35,208
and then your gate regains
some of its strength back.

201
00:08:35,291 --> 00:08:36,666
- [groans]

202
00:08:37,291 --> 00:08:40,083
Sorry, I guess I've caused you
some trouble, haven't I?

203
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,416
- I don't think you understand,
Subaru.

204
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:44,458
- Huh?

205
00:08:44,541 --> 00:08:46,375
- It's infinitely
more satisfying

206
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:48,333
to hear a single thank you than
to be subjected to a barrage

207
00:08:48,416 --> 00:08:51,041
of sorry after sorry.

208
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:52,875
I did it because I wanted
to help you,

209
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:55,291
not because I was looking
for an apology.

210
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:56,333
Okay?

211
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:57,958
- [gasps]

212
00:08:58,916 --> 00:09:00,333
[distant wolves howling]

213
00:09:00,416 --> 00:09:02,708
- So, given what you've seen
of our new guest

214
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:03,750
and everything he can do so far,

215
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:06,708
what do you think of him,
dear Ram?

216
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:08,416
- In terms of abilities,

217
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:09,916
he's completely incompetent,

218
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:13,125
but he can be excessively
quick-witted when it counts. I

219
00:09:13,208 --> 00:09:15,416
believe it may be necessary
to keep an eye

220
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:17,000
on him for a time.

221
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:18,833
- This is a problem
we must handle

222
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:21,166
with the utmost care
and caution.

223
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:24,000
And I ask that you be sure
to give the proper warnings

224
00:09:24,083 --> 00:09:27,166
<i>to your sister so that</i>
<i>she doesn't act rashly.</i>

225
00:09:29,125 --> 00:09:31,500
- I guess that's about all
I can expect of the first day.

226
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:34,791
I earned quite a bit of trust
from Ram and Rem, I think.

227
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:36,125
Way to go.

228
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:38,833
But the bigger problem here
is that shaman's attack.

229
00:09:38,916 --> 00:09:40,750
How do we go
about fighting that?

230
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:45,625
- You want to know more
about shamans, I suppose?

231
00:09:45,708 --> 00:09:49,000
- Yeah, like how do you
avoid curses, for instance?

232
00:09:49,083 --> 00:09:50,750
- There is no way
to do so.

233
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:51,791
- Huh?

234
00:09:51,875 --> 00:09:53,541
- It's impossible
to undo a curse

235
00:09:53,625 --> 00:09:56,125
once it's been activated,
I suppose.

236
00:09:56,208 --> 00:09:58,083
Once they've begun,
that's it.

237
00:09:58,166 --> 00:09:59,500
That's what curses are.

238
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:03,041
- It's possible to nullify
instant death resistances?

239
00:10:03,125 --> 00:10:05,500
- However,
before they're activated,

240
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:07,416
curses are nothing more
than simple spells,

241
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,041
so I can easily undo them.

242
00:10:09,125 --> 00:10:10,208
[grunts]

243
00:10:10,291 --> 00:10:11,500
[sniffing]

244
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:13,500
That is the Witch's scent.

245
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:16,208
- You know,
Rem mentioned that, too.

246
00:10:16,291 --> 00:10:17,791
Who is this witch?

247
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:20,625
Are all of these witches related
to shamans in any way?

248
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:25,041
- In this world,
when one says the word witch,

249
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:27,875
they're really just referring
to one person in particular.

250
00:10:29,583 --> 00:10:31,166
- The Witch of Envy, right?

251
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:32,041
- Exactly.

252
00:10:32,125 --> 00:10:34,250
The Witch of Envy, Satella.

253
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,583
Long ago she devoured
the six witches

254
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:38,416
who bore the names
of the deadly sins

255
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,916
and drained half
the world dry.

256
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,250
She's pretty much the worst
of the worst, I suppose.

257
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:43,208
- [gasps]

258
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:44,500
- The story goes that she

259
00:10:44,583 --> 00:10:45,916
was starved for love.

260
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:49,208
It's said that she doesn't
understand human language.

261
00:10:49,291 --> 00:10:52,166
It's also been said that her
body never withers from age,

262
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:54,416
weakens from sickness,
or dies.

263
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:57,166
And although she was sealed
by the powers of a dragon,

264
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,541
a hero,
and a sage,

265
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,250
they were still never able
to destroy her flesh.

266
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:04,333
It's said that her body
is that of a half elf

267
00:11:04,416 --> 00:11:06,125
with silver hair.

268
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:08,250
- [grunts]

269
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:12,333
- It's Satella.

270
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:15,458
- What would it take
to make somebody steal

271
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:17,500
the Witch of Envy's name?
Hang on.

272
00:11:17,583 --> 00:11:19,083
I guess "steal" makes
the person sound bad.

273
00:11:19,166 --> 00:11:22,000
Maybe I should say to make
somebody borrow the Witch

274
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:24,083
of Envy's name instead.
- Either way,

275
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:26,625
they must have no fear of death,
I suppose.

276
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:28,916
One who would steal the name
of the Witch of Envy

277
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,458
can be called nothing
but insane.

278
00:11:30,541 --> 00:11:31,833
- [gasps]

279
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:36,375
I see.

280
00:11:36,458 --> 00:11:38,000
So that's why.
- Huh?

281
00:11:38,083 --> 00:11:39,333
- She wouldn't have
to be involved

282
00:11:39,416 --> 00:11:42,500
in this royal selection mess
if everyone just saw her

283
00:11:42,583 --> 00:11:43,791
as some kind of crazy freak.

284
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:45,625
- What are you talking about?

285
00:11:47,625 --> 00:11:49,333
- Nothing at all.
Don't worry about it.

286
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:52,333
- Good morning!

287
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:53,833
It's another sunny day,

288
00:11:53,916 --> 00:11:55,250
perfect for drying laundry!

289
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:57,208
Let's make this a day filled
with happiness!

290
00:11:57,291 --> 00:12:00,125
Make this a day of victory!

291
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,250
Victory!

292
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:05,166
- You're so energetic again
this morning.

293
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,166
- Yep!

294
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,458
Even as I'm ordered around

295
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:09,000
and disciplined
by the maid sisters,

296
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:11,666
I'll enjoy my life of servitude
to the fullest once again!

297
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:14,291
But when that lifestyle wears me
out--and you know it will--

298
00:12:14,375 --> 00:12:15,750
I'll come rest my head
in your lap

299
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,125
so save it for me, okay?

300
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:18,833
When you wash your face
that way,

301
00:12:18,916 --> 00:12:20,250
you really look like a cat!

302
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:22,708
So, do spirits get sleepy
and worn out?

303
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:23,750
Do they ever oversleep?

304
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,625
- Yeah, don't you people
get sleepy

305
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,125
when you're fatigued, too?

306
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:31,875
Spirits can go through something
that's similar when their mana

307
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:33,833
is depleted.
[yawns]

308
00:12:33,916 --> 00:12:35,041
- [yawns]

309
00:12:35,125 --> 00:12:36,875
- Did you two stay up all night?

310
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:38,666
I bet you were up late talking
about who you like, right?

311
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,666
That's it, isn't it?
Come on!

312
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,541
Let me in on the fun.
Huh?

313
00:12:42,625 --> 00:12:43,875
So who do I like?

314
00:12:43,958 --> 00:12:45,250
Well, it's embarrassing
to say but--

315
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:46,833
- The one that I like is Puck

316
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,791
and the one that Puck likes
is me.

317
00:12:48,875 --> 00:12:50,458
There.
Conversation's over.

318
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:52,875
- It's mutual?
Then where do I fit in?

319
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:54,125
- Nowhere.

320
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:56,625
Lia's head over heels
for my charms.

321
00:12:56,708 --> 00:12:58,916
It's not like you're a bad guy
or anything.

322
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,041
But compared to me
you've got nothing to offer.

323
00:13:01,125 --> 00:13:02,791
- [shouts]
- You should give up on Lia

324
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:04,458
and just--
[both shouting]

325
00:13:04,541 --> 00:13:06,291
- Don't get carried away,
you two.

326
00:13:06,375 --> 00:13:08,958
I'm going to get mad
if you keep up this foolishness.

327
00:13:09,041 --> 00:13:11,041
both: Sorry, sorry!
Didn't mean to make you mad!

328
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:12,291
- Whoopsie!

329
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:13,708
I'd better get going
or the maid sisters

330
00:13:13,791 --> 00:13:16,416
will be angry!
Bye!

331
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:17,500
- [groans]

332
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:19,708
- Mm?
Hey, what's wrong?

333
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:23,083
You don't look very happy.

334
00:13:23,166 --> 00:13:26,291
- I just feel sort of uneasy.

335
00:13:26,375 --> 00:13:28,291
I don't think I can explain it.

336
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:31,916
- Well, I can't exactly blame
you for being confused,

337
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,291
'cause this has gotten
to be kind of a problem.

338
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:37,125
- [gasps]
- Hey, don't worry!

339
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:38,791
Forget about it!
Everything's fine!

340
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:40,166
- What do you mean, problem?

341
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:41,500
- Just relax, okay?

342
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:43,375
I'll clean this up so fast
no one will get hurt.

343
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:44,625
See?
Already done.

344
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:47,875
- What I'm saying
is Subaru's mind is mixed up.

345
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:50,041
The inside and outside
are all jumbled.

346
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:53,916
- I think that attitude of yours
is quite admirable

347
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,708
but you were the one who knocked
it over in the first place.

348
00:13:56,791 --> 00:13:58,458
I'll go find a replacement.

349
00:13:58,541 --> 00:13:59,791
- No, that's okay!

350
00:13:59,875 --> 00:14:01,250
Let me take care
of the vase and flowers!

351
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:02,583
I insist!

352
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:04,666
You can just keep doing
your own work!

353
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:07,916
<i>- If he keeps this state</i>
<i>of confusion going,</i>

354
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,125
<i>he'll wear himself out</i>
<i>before long.</i>

355
00:14:11,708 --> 00:14:14,375
- [exhales sharply]

356
00:14:14,458 --> 00:14:17,166
It feels pretty great
to finish a job, huh, Rem-Rem?

357
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:18,958
- It was work that you created

358
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:21,333
and took care of on your own,
though.

359
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:24,041
When did you learn
where the vases are kept?

360
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:25,458
- [grunts]

361
00:14:25,541 --> 00:14:26,583
- Did my sister--
- That's right!

362
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:28,833
Your sister told me!

363
00:14:28,916 --> 00:14:31,125
Since she knows me and how much
of a klutz I am,

364
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:33,333
she said, "You're bound to break
a vase eventually.

365
00:14:33,416 --> 00:14:35,000
"I'll tell you where
the extra vases are

366
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:36,708
so you'll always be prepared."

367
00:14:36,791 --> 00:14:38,000
[laughs]
- Subaru--

368
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:39,000
- Whoops!

369
00:14:39,083 --> 00:14:40,333
I totally forgot about some work

370
00:14:40,416 --> 00:14:41,666
that Ram asked me to do!

371
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,083
Would you excuse me for a bit?

372
00:14:43,166 --> 00:14:44,333
I can take care of it quick.

373
00:14:44,416 --> 00:14:47,416
See you later!
I'll come find you soon!

374
00:14:48,458 --> 00:14:50,166
<i>I feel sick.</i>

375
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:52,375
[knocking]

376
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:53,625
Don't you think
my knife technique

377
00:14:53,708 --> 00:14:55,500
has come a long way
in just one day?

378
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:57,291
I think my talent
has finally awakened.

379
00:14:57,375 --> 00:14:59,041
<i>I feel sick.</i>
<i>I feel sick.</i>

380
00:14:59,125 --> 00:15:00,375
<i>I feel sick.</i>

381
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:02,666
That makes such amazing
crafting possible.

382
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:05,916
There must be a miracle residing
in my fingertips right now.

383
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,166
Illusion!
<i>I feel sick.</i>

384
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:10,208
<i>I feel sick.</i>
<i>I feel sick.</i>

385
00:15:10,291 --> 00:15:11,458
<i>I feel sick.</i>

386
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:13,250
<i>I feel sick.</i>
Honestly, Mili,

387
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:15,333
every time we meet,
you stir up my heart.

388
00:15:15,416 --> 00:15:18,958
You're such a sinful girl.
You're guilty, I tell ya!

389
00:15:19,041 --> 00:15:21,125
<i>I should be able</i>
<i>to laugh better.</i>

390
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:23,666
<i>I should be able</i>
<i>to make them laugh better.</i>

391
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:25,166
<i>I can't fail this time.</i>

392
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:26,958
<i>I can't waste a single second.</i>

393
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:29,791
<i>I have to throw all my strength</i>
<i>into my work and produce</i>

394
00:15:29,875 --> 00:15:30,833
<i>some kind of results or--</i>
[gasps]

395
00:15:30,916 --> 00:15:33,625
Oh, Ram!
I wasn't slacking.

396
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:35,541
I'll finish up all my work.
Just you wait.

397
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:37,541
Now, why don't you go kick back
in your room

398
00:15:37,625 --> 00:15:38,500
and take a well-earned siesta
while I--

399
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:43,500
[vomiting]

400
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:46,125
[gasping]

401
00:15:46,208 --> 00:15:48,208
Damn, I look so lame.

402
00:15:48,291 --> 00:15:52,000
I don't have time to spend
whining like this.

403
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:54,041
You idiot.

404
00:15:54,125 --> 00:15:56,375
[grunts]

405
00:15:56,458 --> 00:15:57,541
- Subaru?
- [grunts]

406
00:15:57,625 --> 00:15:58,958
[chuckles]

407
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,333
Mili!
- Subaru.

408
00:16:01,416 --> 00:16:02,375
Come with me.
- Uh-oh!

409
00:16:02,458 --> 00:16:04,750
A personal invitation?
From Mili?

410
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:06,083
This is moving so fast.

411
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:07,666
How joyous.
How embarrassing.

412
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:08,791
How rare!
Say anything.

413
00:16:08,875 --> 00:16:10,250
Tell me to do anything.

414
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:11,916
For you I'd dive into fire,
water, the loot house, anywhere!

415
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,916
- Listen to me.
- [grunts]

416
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,125
Hey, come on.

417
00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:17,500
The Mili I know would never
be so cold.

418
00:16:17,583 --> 00:16:19,625
Wait, are you some kind of fake?

419
00:16:19,708 --> 00:16:21,000
No way.
That's impossible!

420
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:22,291
How could anyone else be capable
of looking so gorgeous

421
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:25,208
that when I see her all I want
to do is hug her?

422
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:27,250
- All right.

423
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,666
Subaru, you heard me.
- Wha--

424
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,125
- Let's go.

425
00:16:31,208 --> 00:16:33,000
Now sit down right here.

426
00:16:33,083 --> 00:16:35,375
- Can't I sit on the bed
or a chair?

427
00:16:35,458 --> 00:16:37,000
Why does it have
to be the floor?

428
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:38,291
- Just sit down!

429
00:16:38,375 --> 00:16:39,708
- With pleasure!
Right away!

430
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:40,958
Yes, ma'am.

431
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:43,208
- [grunts]

432
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,500
Only this once, all right?

433
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:55,625
- Huh?

434
00:16:56,916 --> 00:16:58,666
[grunts]

435
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,500
- Your position
is a little weird,

436
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:03,166
and it tickles a bit.

437
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:05,916
- I can rest in your lap?

438
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,416
- Don't say that out loud!
It's embarrassing!

439
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:11,000
And no looking up here.
Face the wall.

440
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:12,333
Close your eyes.

441
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:14,625
- You're even more adorable
when you're embarrassed,

442
00:17:14,708 --> 00:17:18,291
but why did you suddenly let
me do this, anyway?

443
00:17:18,375 --> 00:17:20,458
I mean, when did I do something
worthy enough

444
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:22,250
to earn a reward this awesome?

445
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,208
- Enough of that
weird tough act.

446
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:27,041
You don't need
to do that right now.

447
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:29,166
Isn't this what you wanted?

448
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:32,291
Didn't you tell me to lend you
my lap when you were exhausted?

449
00:17:33,208 --> 00:17:35,291
I can't do this all the time,

450
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:36,833
but today is special.

451
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:39,375
- Hey, it's only my second day
of working here.

452
00:17:39,458 --> 00:17:40,916
If I'm already completely
worn out,

453
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,458
what kind of weakling am I?

454
00:17:43,541 --> 00:17:46,791
- It's plain to see that you're
overwhelmed about something.

455
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:50,375
But you're not going to tell me
what's really going on, are you?

456
00:17:51,291 --> 00:17:54,708
I don't know if doing this will
make things any easier for you,

457
00:17:54,791 --> 00:17:57,958
but if it helps at all,
I'm happy to.

458
00:17:58,041 --> 00:18:00,250
- [chuckles]

459
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:02,291
Mili, come on now.

460
00:18:02,375 --> 00:18:03,708
You don't have to.

461
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:05,333
- Are you tired?

462
00:18:05,416 --> 00:18:08,333
- No, I'm totally fine, really.

463
00:18:08,416 --> 00:18:10,041
- Do you feel troubled?

464
00:18:10,125 --> 00:18:12,916
- If you're this nice to me,
I'm gonna fall in love with you.

465
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,958
When you--I mean,
like that.

466
00:18:16,875 --> 00:18:18,375
- It's been rough.

467
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:20,541
Hasn't it?

468
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,666
<i>[Rie Takahashi's</i>
<i>"Bouya no Yume yo"]</i>

469
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:31,000
- Yeah, it was rough.

470
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:33,416
And it was so painful.

471
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,291
I was just so terrified.

472
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:37,083
I was so sad, it hurt.

473
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:38,916
It hurt so much.

474
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:39,708
I thought I'd die.

475
00:18:39,791 --> 00:18:41,541
- [grunts]

476
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:43,166
- I tried so hard and I--
[sniffs]

477
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:45,750
I couldn't get things
to work out!

478
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:49,083
I was so desperate
to set things right.

479
00:18:49,166 --> 00:18:52,458
So desperate to make everything
turn out okay!

480
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:53,375
It's the truth.

481
00:18:53,458 --> 00:18:56,583
I honestly never tried so hard

482
00:18:56,666 --> 00:18:58,875
to do anything
in my entire life!

483
00:18:58,958 --> 00:19:00,041
- Mm.

484
00:19:00,125 --> 00:19:01,750
Yes, I know.

485
00:19:01,833 --> 00:19:03,250
- [crying]

486
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:06,041
Because I love this place
so much.

487
00:19:06,125 --> 00:19:08,166
Because it was so important
to me.

488
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:09,958
I was so scared.

489
00:19:10,041 --> 00:19:14,291
I just--I was so desperate
to set everything right again.

490
00:19:14,375 --> 00:19:18,250
I didn't want those eyes looking
at me like that.

491
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:21,208
It was so completely terrifying.

492
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:24,500
And I hated myself so much.
[crying]

493
00:19:24,583 --> 00:19:26,791
So much for feeling that way!

494
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:29,791
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

495
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:36,916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

496
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:42,166
- Subaru?
[gasps]

497
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:43,750
- [shushes]

498
00:19:44,458 --> 00:19:46,958
- Is he just asleep or--

499
00:19:47,041 --> 00:19:49,583
- Yes.
[giggles]

500
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:51,500
He looks like a child,
doesn't he?

501
00:19:52,083 --> 00:19:53,916
- A little bit but he definitely
looks like he can't do

502
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,416
any more work today.

503
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:57,541
- You're right there.

504
00:19:57,625 --> 00:19:59,250
Think he's done for the day.

505
00:19:59,875 --> 00:20:02,083
What a bad boy,
taking all this time off

506
00:20:02,166 --> 00:20:04,375
on his second day working here.

507
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:07,625
When he feels better,
you can punish him, then.

508
00:20:07,708 --> 00:20:10,875
- When I see him like this,
I almost don't want to.

509
00:20:10,958 --> 00:20:13,666
- [chuckles]

510
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:17,166
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

511
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,875
- I'll go inform my sister

512
00:20:18,958 --> 00:20:20,500
that Subaru will be useless
for today.

513
00:20:21,166 --> 00:20:23,083
- Rem.
- Huh?

514
00:20:23,166 --> 00:20:25,333
- Subaru is a good boy.

515
00:20:30,291 --> 00:20:32,083
[footsteps walking away]

516
00:20:36,166 --> 00:20:37,416
<i>- No, please!</i>

517
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,458
<i>Did I really just bawl all over</i>
<i>the girl I love</i>

518
00:20:39,541 --> 00:20:42,083
<i>and fall asleep with tears</i>
<i>and snot all over my face?</i>

519
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:45,416
Oh, man, I'm so ashamed!
I'm totally hopeless!

520
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:46,583
What a loser.

521
00:20:46,666 --> 00:20:47,666
- You burst in here late
at night

522
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:49,291
and that's what you say,
I suppose?

523
00:20:49,375 --> 00:20:52,666
- Don't say that, Beako!
We're tight, aren't we?

524
00:20:52,750 --> 00:20:54,375
Oh!
- What kind of relationship

525
00:20:54,458 --> 00:20:57,041
do you think we--
wait a sec.

526
00:20:57,125 --> 00:20:58,833
What did you just call me?

527
00:20:58,916 --> 00:21:00,333
- Oh, Beako?

528
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:02,333
Well, I think pet names
are indispensable

529
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,250
when it comes to showing
affection for others.

530
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:06,500
So I've decided that's what
I'm gonna call you.

531
00:21:06,583 --> 00:21:09,166
It's the best proof of my
affection that I can give.

532
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:11,458
What do you think?
- What a ridiculous display

533
00:21:11,541 --> 00:21:13,833
of goodwill.
That isn't just disgusting.

534
00:21:13,916 --> 00:21:15,541
It's revolting.
[scoffs]

535
00:21:15,625 --> 00:21:17,916
- Come on.
Don't be so cold, Beako.

536
00:21:18,541 --> 00:21:19,583
The thing is...

537
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:23,500
I'm really backed into a corner.

538
00:21:23,583 --> 00:21:25,166
I need your help
with those curses,

539
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:26,375
to be honest with you.

540
00:21:26,458 --> 00:21:28,083
- Told you curses
can't be undone

541
00:21:28,166 --> 00:21:29,541
once they're activated,
I suppose.

542
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:31,000
- That's right.
I remember.

543
00:21:31,083 --> 00:21:33,208
But would it be possible
for you to detect them

544
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:34,958
before they've
been activated instead?

545
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:38,083
- I am capable of discovering
curses before that happens,

546
00:21:38,166 --> 00:21:40,125
I suppose.
- [gasps]

547
00:21:41,291 --> 00:21:43,541
So how are they placed, anyway?

548
00:21:43,625 --> 00:21:45,666
- There is one rule
of casting curses

549
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,791
that cannot be broken,
I suppose.

550
00:21:47,875 --> 00:21:49,166
- A rule that can't be broken?

551
00:21:49,791 --> 00:21:53,291
- Physical contact with
the target of the curse.

552
00:21:53,375 --> 00:21:54,958
That is the single prerequisite.

553
00:21:55,041 --> 00:21:56,333
- [gasps]

554
00:21:56,416 --> 00:21:58,875
So far the only people
I've touched other than the ones

555
00:21:58,958 --> 00:22:00,166
in this mansion
are the villagers

556
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:01,625
at the base of the mountain.

557
00:22:02,458 --> 00:22:03,958
I was cursed in the village

558
00:22:04,041 --> 00:22:06,458
and then it activated
in the mansion that night.

559
00:22:06,541 --> 00:22:08,291
And after that I died?

560
00:22:09,083 --> 00:22:10,750
That would explain why
the shaman was able

561
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:12,250
to get Rem the last time around.

562
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:14,125
<i>I didn't go to the village</i>

563
00:22:14,208 --> 00:22:16,500
<i>so she ended up being</i>
<i>the target.</i>

564
00:22:17,083 --> 00:22:18,291
Yes, that fits.

565
00:22:18,375 --> 00:22:20,125
Everything fits now.

566
00:22:20,208 --> 00:22:21,958
I finally found a lead!

567
00:22:22,041 --> 00:22:24,208
Hell yeah!

568
00:22:24,291 --> 00:22:26,708
- Is that any attitude to take
towards someone you asked

569
00:22:26,791 --> 00:22:28,000
for help,
I suppose?

570
00:22:28,083 --> 00:22:30,166
If my insight
was beneficial to you,

571
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:32,000
I think there's something
you should say.

572
00:22:32,083 --> 00:22:33,666
- Wait, of course!
That's right!

573
00:22:33,750 --> 00:22:35,333
Thanks for your help!

574
00:22:35,416 --> 00:22:37,458
I can finally see the light!
Yes!

575
00:22:37,541 --> 00:22:40,458
Beako, I love you!

576
00:22:40,541 --> 00:22:43,000
- Put me down now!
- [screams]

577
00:22:44,583 --> 00:22:48,000
[birds chirping]

578
00:22:48,083 --> 00:22:50,458
- And so in summary,
a lot's happened,

579
00:22:50,541 --> 00:22:52,333
but today's a fresh start.
I'm a new me!

580
00:22:52,416 --> 00:22:55,250
- The lap pillow, right?
- Definitely the lap pillow.

581
00:22:55,916 --> 00:22:56,583
- Huh?

582
00:22:56,666 --> 00:22:58,750
Wait, you guys knew?

583
00:22:58,833 --> 00:23:01,125
- [grunts]
Good morning, Subaru.

584
00:23:01,208 --> 00:23:02,208
- Oh, Mili.

585
00:23:02,875 --> 00:23:07,208
- Well, this is
a little embarrassing, but...

586
00:23:08,833 --> 00:23:10,583
Are you feeling okay today?

587
00:23:10,666 --> 00:23:13,333
- I wasn't completely sure until
I heard your voice just then,

588
00:23:13,416 --> 00:23:14,791
but--
[inhales sharply]

589
00:23:15,416 --> 00:23:18,541
[exhales]
Yes, I'm okay now.

590
00:23:18,625 --> 00:23:21,125
So, um, listen, Mili.

591
00:23:21,208 --> 00:23:23,916
I'm sorry about what happened.

592
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,125
[chuckles]

593
00:23:25,208 --> 00:23:27,208
No, I mean thanks
for everything.

594
00:23:27,291 --> 00:23:27,958
- [chuckles]

595
00:23:28,041 --> 00:23:30,166
Of course.

596
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:33,125
You're most welcome, Subaru.

597
00:23:33,208 --> 00:23:35,291
Well, are you ready
to get started

598
00:23:35,375 --> 00:23:36,541
on this morning's work?

599
00:23:36,625 --> 00:23:38,750
We need to begin our list
of morning duties.

600
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:41,416
- [grunts]
Before all that,

601
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:42,916
I have a favor to ask of you.

602
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,333
- Lap pillow, right?
- It's a lap pillow.

603
00:23:44,416 --> 00:23:47,000
- I'm not that much of a perv!

604
00:23:47,083 --> 00:23:49,125
Actually, I want to go
to the village.

605
00:23:49,208 --> 00:23:50,791
It's not far, right?

606
00:23:50,875 --> 00:23:52,541
Do we have any plans
to go shopping for anything?

607
00:23:52,625 --> 00:23:55,458
- Actually,
if I recall correctly,

608
00:23:55,541 --> 00:23:57,833
we're low on seasonings,
so I was thinking of going

609
00:23:57,916 --> 00:23:59,083
to the village tomorrow.

610
00:23:59,166 --> 00:24:00,875
- Then why don't we just go
today instead?

611
00:24:00,958 --> 00:24:01,958
I mean, if we're running low,

612
00:24:02,041 --> 00:24:03,625
it never hurts
to restock sooner.

613
00:24:03,708 --> 00:24:05,041
- Hmm.

614
00:24:06,166 --> 00:24:07,875
- I don't see a problem
with that at all.

615
00:24:07,958 --> 00:24:09,208
- Are you sure, sister?

616
00:24:09,291 --> 00:24:10,666
- You do need to go shopping

617
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:11,916
and we have no urgent duties
right now.

618
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:15,416
Plus you have Barusu
to carry your packages.

619
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,541
- All right,
if you say so, sister.

620
00:24:17,625 --> 00:24:18,833
- Yes!

621
00:24:18,916 --> 00:24:22,291
- However, I'm coming along
with you.

622
00:24:22,375 --> 00:24:24,583
You'll have a pretty flower
on each arm, Barusu.

623
00:24:24,666 --> 00:24:25,875
- Huh?

624
00:24:25,958 --> 00:24:29,750
I'm just hoping those flowers
aren't poisonous.

625
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:37,916
- And now for
the final exercise.

626
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,250
Swing your arms out wide.

627
00:24:40,333 --> 00:24:42,541
Then cross them in front of you
as you take slow,

628
00:24:42,625 --> 00:24:44,500
deep breaths.

629
00:24:44,583 --> 00:24:48,250
- Well, I came to check on him
since break time's almost over.

630
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:49,375
- Things are quite lively here.

631
00:24:49,458 --> 00:24:53,583
- Now, big finish.
Victory!

632
00:24:53,666 --> 00:24:55,291
all: Victory!

633
00:24:56,250 --> 00:24:58,000
[all shouting]

634
00:24:58,083 --> 00:24:59,875
All right!
- Yeah!

635
00:24:59,958 --> 00:25:01,750
[both laughing]

636
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:04,041
- [gasps]
- I feel so much younger

637
00:25:04,125 --> 00:25:05,625
after that.
[laughs]

638
00:25:05,708 --> 00:25:08,625
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

639
00:25:08,708 --> 00:25:11,291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

640
00:25:11,375 --> 00:25:14,291
<i>- Okay, everyone</i>
<i>has touched me now.</i>

641
00:25:14,375 --> 00:25:15,750
- Barusu.
- [grunts]

642
00:25:15,833 --> 00:25:17,750
- Exactly what sort
of game is this?

643
00:25:17,833 --> 00:25:19,416
- Radio calisthenics.

644
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:22,791
I think the fact that everyone
young and old can enjoy it

645
00:25:22,875 --> 00:25:26,000
is the key secret to its many
long years of success.

646
00:25:26,083 --> 00:25:27,333
- Who cares?

647
00:25:27,416 --> 00:25:28,916
- Ram-Ram, that was cold.

648
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,833
- Ram-Ram, that was mean.
- Ram-Ram, you're scary.

649
00:25:33,791 --> 00:25:35,291
- Did you teach
all these children

650
00:25:35,375 --> 00:25:36,583
to call me by that name?

651
00:25:36,666 --> 00:25:37,833
- Well, it was more like,

652
00:25:37,916 --> 00:25:40,458
I wanted to share some
friendliness around

653
00:25:40,541 --> 00:25:41,416
with everybody.
- [exhales]

654
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:43,833
I suppose I don't mind it.

655
00:25:43,916 --> 00:25:45,166
What about Rem?

656
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:47,625
- You mean Rem-Rim?
- She's Rem-Rim.

657
00:25:47,708 --> 00:25:48,708
- Or Rem-Rim Rem-Rim.

658
00:25:48,791 --> 00:25:50,916
- [gasps]

659
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,750
- [sighs]
So then,

660
00:25:52,833 --> 00:25:54,833
enjoy the village trip
you wanted so much?

661
00:25:54,916 --> 00:25:57,291
- I sure did.
Nothing to worry about there.

662
00:25:57,375 --> 00:25:59,541
When Muraosa patted my shoulder
at the end,

663
00:25:59,625 --> 00:26:00,875
my trip was complete.

664
00:26:01,375 --> 00:26:02,875
[grunts]
What's up?

665
00:26:02,958 --> 00:26:05,625
If you wanna say something
then just tell me.

666
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,708
- Uh, take a look.

667
00:26:09,791 --> 00:26:11,083
Over there.

668
00:26:11,166 --> 00:26:13,166
- [grunts]

669
00:26:15,708 --> 00:26:16,958
[grunts]

670
00:26:17,041 --> 00:26:19,166
- All right, have your way
a little bit longer.

671
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:21,250
- Well, if you say so, sister.

672
00:26:21,333 --> 00:26:25,000
- Yes, really appreciate it,
my dear senpais.

673
00:26:32,041 --> 00:26:34,250
That's right.
There was an event like this.

674
00:26:34,333 --> 00:26:36,041
I remember.

675
00:26:36,583 --> 00:26:37,625
[dog snarls]

676
00:26:37,708 --> 00:26:39,583
And this little pup
still hates me.

677
00:26:39,666 --> 00:26:41,416
- Weird.
She's usually so tame.

678
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:43,250
- She only growls like that
at Subaru.

679
00:26:43,333 --> 00:26:45,416
- What'd you do to make her
so mad at you?

680
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:47,291
- I wish I knew the answer
to that one.

681
00:26:47,375 --> 00:26:48,458
Believe me.

682
00:26:48,541 --> 00:26:49,875
If it's happened three times,

683
00:26:49,958 --> 00:26:52,000
I guess we're just incompatible.

684
00:26:52,083 --> 00:26:53,500
Oh, now's my chance!

685
00:26:53,583 --> 00:26:55,625
If you'll excuse me.

686
00:26:57,333 --> 00:26:58,333
[giggles]

687
00:26:58,416 --> 00:26:59,500
There's the sensation
I've longed for.

688
00:26:59,583 --> 00:27:00,666
You know,
for a stray,

689
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:03,333
your fur feels pretty
fantastic, pup.

690
00:27:03,416 --> 00:27:06,375
Hey, you've got a big bald spot
on top of your head.

691
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:08,000
Is it a scar?

692
00:27:08,083 --> 00:27:11,000
What did you walk int--
Yeow!

693
00:27:11,083 --> 00:27:13,541
You even bit me in almost
the same exact spot.

694
00:27:13,625 --> 00:27:15,416
Are you a time traveling canine?

695
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:16,916
[snarls]

696
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:18,541
- Guess she got carried away.

697
00:27:18,625 --> 00:27:20,666
- It's what you get
for touching her so much.

698
00:27:20,750 --> 00:27:22,333
- She is a girl, after all.

699
00:27:22,416 --> 00:27:23,750
- I really don't think that's
the problem here.

700
00:27:23,833 --> 00:27:26,833
Also, isn't anybody worried
about me?

701
00:27:26,916 --> 00:27:28,458
I was just bitten, you know.

702
00:27:28,541 --> 00:27:30,000
[all laughing]

703
00:27:31,416 --> 00:27:33,208
Holy crap, I made it.

704
00:27:33,291 --> 00:27:35,166
Well done, me.
Good job.

705
00:27:35,250 --> 00:27:36,666
Seriously,
really nice work there.

706
00:27:36,750 --> 00:27:38,666
- Yes, yes.
Job well done.

707
00:27:38,750 --> 00:27:40,416
- Yes, yes.
Excellent work.

708
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:42,208
- Ah, I see the three
of you are together.

709
00:27:42,291 --> 00:27:44,375
Good.

710
00:27:44,458 --> 00:27:47,000
That will save me precious time
on my way out.

711
00:27:47,083 --> 00:27:48,125
both: Lord Roswaal.

712
00:27:48,208 --> 00:27:50,250
- Pretty fancy clothes
you got there.

713
00:27:50,333 --> 00:27:52,708
Nice.
- Thank you so much.

714
00:27:52,791 --> 00:27:54,250
I'm getting together
with someone

715
00:27:54,333 --> 00:27:57,208
who's absolutely dreadful
to deal with in normal attire.

716
00:27:57,291 --> 00:28:00,250
So I had no choice but to wear
dress clothes for the occasion.

717
00:28:00,333 --> 00:28:01,708
- Is it a visitor?

718
00:28:01,791 --> 00:28:02,875
- Or will you be going out?

719
00:28:02,958 --> 00:28:04,583
- Ram is correct.

720
00:28:04,666 --> 00:28:06,083
I'll be going out.

721
00:28:06,166 --> 00:28:08,916
I received a message earlier
today that was a tad troublesome

722
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:12,166
so now I'm off to make
the rounds outside.

723
00:28:12,250 --> 00:28:13,541
- [grunts]
- There's a fairly

724
00:28:13,625 --> 00:28:16,500
high likelihood that I won't
be back home tonight.

725
00:28:16,583 --> 00:28:19,208
Ram, Rem, take care of things
until I return.

726
00:28:19,291 --> 00:28:21,000
- Yes sir.
We will do as you command.

727
00:28:21,083 --> 00:28:23,791
- Yes, sir,
even if it costs our lives.

728
00:28:23,875 --> 00:28:25,416
<i>-- Roswaal didn't leave</i>
<i>the mansion</i>

729
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:26,958
<i>any of those times before.</i>

730
00:28:27,041 --> 00:28:28,625
[grunts]

731
00:28:29,208 --> 00:28:31,958
- I've great expectations
for you, too, Subaru.

732
00:28:32,041 --> 00:28:34,208
I want you to keep an eye
on Miss Emilia

733
00:28:34,291 --> 00:28:36,208
and take good care of her.

734
00:28:36,583 --> 00:28:39,291
- Sure, you can definitely count
on me for that.

735
00:28:41,666 --> 00:28:44,791
- Look after things
while I'm away, everyone.

736
00:28:45,625 --> 00:28:47,708
- Whoa, Roswaal can fly?

737
00:28:47,791 --> 00:28:49,166
[whooshing]

738
00:28:55,250 --> 00:28:57,125
Magic in incredible.

739
00:29:00,666 --> 00:29:03,708
<i>The difference in circumstances</i>
<i>from my previous experiences</i>

740
00:29:03,791 --> 00:29:05,833
<i>of this day must have been</i>
<i>triggered by my visit</i>

741
00:29:05,916 --> 00:29:07,208
<i>to the village.</i>

742
00:29:07,291 --> 00:29:08,833
<i>That means my strategy</i>
<i>of acting</i>

743
00:29:08,916 --> 00:29:10,875
<i>as a decoy is working</i>
<i>as planned.</i>

744
00:29:13,916 --> 00:29:17,500
And that's why I'm here
for my long-awaited Beako time.

745
00:29:17,583 --> 00:29:19,416
- Your face looks quite
different than it did

746
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:20,500
half a day ago.

747
00:29:20,583 --> 00:29:21,958
You've been busy,
I suppose.

748
00:29:22,041 --> 00:29:24,791
- I'd love to take it easy
for a change, you know?

749
00:29:24,875 --> 00:29:26,958
But I can't 'cause there's
something I want you

750
00:29:27,041 --> 00:29:28,958
to check out for me.

751
00:29:29,041 --> 00:29:30,458
I think I've been cursed.

752
00:29:30,541 --> 00:29:33,125
Could you look me over head
to toe and find out for sure?

753
00:29:33,708 --> 00:29:34,833
- What are you talking about?

754
00:29:34,916 --> 00:29:36,500
- I think I've been cursed.

755
00:29:36,583 --> 00:29:38,458
Could you look me over head
to toe and find out for sure?

756
00:29:38,541 --> 00:29:41,333
- Ah, no, you don't have
to repeat yourself, I suppose.

757
00:29:41,416 --> 00:29:43,125
It hasn't even been a full day

758
00:29:43,208 --> 00:29:44,833
since I first told you
about shamans.

759
00:29:44,916 --> 00:29:47,375
You're far too
impressionable for--

760
00:29:48,083 --> 00:29:49,625
Wait just a minute.

761
00:29:50,291 --> 00:29:52,041
You really have been cursed,
I suppose.

762
00:29:52,125 --> 00:29:53,791
- So it turns out the shaman

763
00:29:53,875 --> 00:29:56,208
was one of the villagers
after all.

764
00:29:56,291 --> 00:29:58,708
Think you'll be able to figure
out what kind of curse it is?

765
00:29:58,791 --> 00:30:02,125
Well, that wouldn't be possible
simply by looking at it.

766
00:30:02,208 --> 00:30:04,625
But as I told you
a little earlier today,

767
00:30:04,708 --> 00:30:06,000
once it's been activated,

768
00:30:06,083 --> 00:30:07,916
chances are you'll die,
I suppose.

769
00:30:11,583 --> 00:30:12,541
How strange.

770
00:30:12,625 --> 00:30:14,000
Even after that reminder,

771
00:30:14,083 --> 00:30:15,500
you don't seem afraid
of dying at all.

772
00:30:15,583 --> 00:30:17,250
- Huh?
Are you out of your mind?

773
00:30:17,333 --> 00:30:19,041
I'm insanely scared of dying.

774
00:30:19,125 --> 00:30:21,083
There's nothing in the world
that freaks me out more

775
00:30:21,166 --> 00:30:22,541
than even thinking about it.

776
00:30:22,625 --> 00:30:24,166
Wish people who say,
"I'd rather die,"

777
00:30:24,250 --> 00:30:26,583
would actually die before
saying stuff like that.

778
00:30:26,666 --> 00:30:28,250
Which is why...

779
00:30:29,083 --> 00:30:31,541
This time I'm determined
to find a way out...

780
00:30:32,791 --> 00:30:33,708
Of this fate.

781
00:30:34,291 --> 00:30:37,625
Okay, so get rid of this curse
for me, would you?

782
00:30:37,708 --> 00:30:39,291
I'm running out of time here.

783
00:30:39,375 --> 00:30:41,333
- Now why should I have
to go through the trouble

784
00:30:41,416 --> 00:30:43,125
of saving your life,
I suppose?

785
00:30:43,208 --> 00:30:45,833
I expected an unlovable
and cold response like that.

786
00:30:45,916 --> 00:30:48,250
So I came fully prepared
to convince you.

787
00:30:48,708 --> 00:30:51,625
If I die, your dearest Puck
is bound to be sad.

788
00:30:52,083 --> 00:30:53,208
- Hmm?

789
00:30:53,291 --> 00:30:55,125
You think too highly
of yourself.

790
00:30:55,208 --> 00:30:56,666
Bubby wouldn't be all
that disturbed if you died.

791
00:30:56,750 --> 00:30:58,416
- Oh, on the contrary.

792
00:30:58,500 --> 00:31:01,666
If I did then Emilia would be
at least a little bit shocked

793
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:03,541
and when Emilia
feels shock like that,

794
00:31:03,625 --> 00:31:05,000
Puck takes damage, too.

795
00:31:05,083 --> 00:31:06,708
If you had the chance
to have stopped it

796
00:31:06,791 --> 00:31:08,666
and chose not to,
what would he think of you?

797
00:31:08,750 --> 00:31:10,083
- [groans]

798
00:31:10,166 --> 00:31:13,125
All right, I'll go along
with your smooth talk this time.

799
00:31:13,208 --> 00:31:14,583
But when all of this is over,

800
00:31:14,666 --> 00:31:16,833
I won't have anything to do
with you again, I suppose.

801
00:31:16,916 --> 00:31:18,291
- [chuckles]

802
00:31:18,375 --> 00:31:20,458
Okay, but I'll always come back
to ask for your help

803
00:31:20,541 --> 00:31:22,125
when I'm in trouble.

804
00:31:23,125 --> 00:31:24,083
- [grunts]

805
00:31:24,166 --> 00:31:25,250
I'll destroy the spell that

806
00:31:25,333 --> 00:31:26,333
was used in the curse now,

807
00:31:26,416 --> 00:31:27,916
I suppose.

808
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:30,416
It's burned into you on
the exact spot on your body

809
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:32,208
that the shaman touched
while casting it.

810
00:31:32,291 --> 00:31:33,083
So that'll act as our reference.

811
00:31:33,166 --> 00:31:35,291
- Yeah, I prepared for this.

812
00:31:35,375 --> 00:31:37,083
I've got it covered.

813
00:31:37,166 --> 00:31:38,875
<i>The young men's leader</i>
<i>with the short hair.</i>

814
00:31:38,958 --> 00:31:41,083
<i>The old lady who petted my butt.</i>

815
00:31:41,166 --> 00:31:43,458
<i>And Muraosa,</i>
<i>the fake village head.</i>

816
00:31:43,541 --> 00:31:46,666
I made sure all the suspects
touched different parts of me.

817
00:31:46,750 --> 00:31:49,583
<i>[tense music]</i>

818
00:31:49,666 --> 00:31:51,291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

819
00:31:51,375 --> 00:31:52,875
[grunts]

820
00:31:52,958 --> 00:31:56,125
[whirring]

821
00:31:59,166 --> 00:32:00,250
Black mist.
Creepy.

822
00:32:00,333 --> 00:32:03,375
- Abhorrent is more like it,
I suppose.

823
00:32:03,458 --> 00:32:05,375
- [gasps]

824
00:32:05,458 --> 00:32:06,750
- There we go.
All done.

825
00:32:06,833 --> 00:32:07,791
So relax.

826
00:32:07,875 --> 00:32:09,791
You'll be just fine now,
I suppose.

827
00:32:11,208 --> 00:32:13,416
- So the place that
the black mist came from,

828
00:32:13,500 --> 00:32:15,750
that's also the spot where
the shaman touched me earlier,

829
00:32:15,833 --> 00:32:17,083
isn't it?

830
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,625
Could that puppy actually be...

831
00:32:24,041 --> 00:32:26,333
I have to get to the village.

832
00:32:26,416 --> 00:32:29,000
They just keep messing with me!

833
00:32:29,083 --> 00:32:30,916
You're gonna pay for this!

834
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:34,125
- The village?
What for?

835
00:32:34,208 --> 00:32:36,416
- Beatrice said that the one
who gave me this wound

836
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:37,958
is also the one
who's responsible

837
00:32:38,041 --> 00:32:39,500
for placing the curse on me.

838
00:32:39,583 --> 00:32:41,958
And that means it was the dog
that the kids were playing with.

839
00:32:42,041 --> 00:32:43,166
[both gasp]

840
00:32:43,250 --> 00:32:44,875
It may have looked innocent
at the time,

841
00:32:44,958 --> 00:32:46,916
but that little beast
cursed everyone it bit.

842
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:48,125
If I don't do something,

843
00:32:48,208 --> 00:32:49,791
they'll be in grave danger.

844
00:32:51,083 --> 00:32:52,291
If you don't think
you can trust me

845
00:32:52,375 --> 00:32:53,625
you're welcome to come along.

846
00:32:53,708 --> 00:32:55,666
But we can't just leave
Emilia defenseless here

847
00:32:55,750 --> 00:32:57,708
all by herself and that means
only one of you can come.

848
00:32:57,791 --> 00:33:00,416
- You made up that rule.

849
00:33:00,500 --> 00:33:03,000
And if we are to obey
Master Roswaal's orders

850
00:33:03,083 --> 00:33:05,208
to the letter then there's
absolutely no reason

851
00:33:05,291 --> 00:33:06,541
for either one of us
to go with you.

852
00:33:06,625 --> 00:33:08,208
- Right, there's not

853
00:33:08,291 --> 00:33:09,250
Fair enough.

854
00:33:09,333 --> 00:33:10,500
But do you happen to recall

855
00:33:10,583 --> 00:33:12,291
the only order Roswaal gave
to me?

856
00:33:13,500 --> 00:33:15,083
- Very well, Barasu.

857
00:33:15,166 --> 00:33:17,416
I will allow you to act
on your best judgment.

858
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:18,625
- But sister--

859
00:33:18,708 --> 00:33:20,416
- And Rem will be
accompanying you.

860
00:33:20,500 --> 00:33:22,333
- Exactly what I wanted to hear.

861
00:33:22,416 --> 00:33:24,625
- That's my decision
so please respect it

862
00:33:24,708 --> 00:33:25,875
and go with him, Rem.

863
00:33:25,958 --> 00:33:27,750
I'll confirm everything
with Miss Beatrice

864
00:33:27,833 --> 00:33:29,375
and remain here
to protect Miss Emilia.

865
00:33:29,458 --> 00:33:32,166
I'll be sure to keep an eye
on other things, too.

866
00:33:32,250 --> 00:33:33,958
- Sister, wait.
You shouldn't--

867
00:33:34,041 --> 00:33:35,833
- Subaru,
are you going somewhere?

868
00:33:35,916 --> 00:33:37,208
I heard voices so I wanted
to come down

869
00:33:37,291 --> 00:33:40,833
and see what was going on.
What happened?

870
00:33:40,916 --> 00:33:43,000
- It's more like something
might be happening.

871
00:33:43,083 --> 00:33:44,458
But you won't need to worry
about all that.

872
00:33:44,541 --> 00:33:47,583
- I'll bet you're going
to do something dangerous again.

873
00:33:47,666 --> 00:33:49,166
- Interestingly enough,
we were just wrapping up

874
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:52,000
a dispute on that
particular subject.

875
00:33:52,583 --> 00:33:54,250
- I can't talk you out
of it, can I?

876
00:33:54,333 --> 00:33:56,958
- [chuckles]
I guess not, no.

877
00:33:57,041 --> 00:33:58,708
As a matter of fact,
if you tried to,

878
00:33:58,791 --> 00:34:00,875
it would be a hindrance
in several ways.

879
00:34:00,958 --> 00:34:02,500
- [sighs]

880
00:34:02,583 --> 00:34:03,791
Fine, fine.
It's okay, I get it.

881
00:34:03,875 --> 00:34:06,541
I won't try to stop you.

882
00:34:06,625 --> 00:34:08,916
It's probably no use telling you
not to be rash

883
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:10,208
or reckless, either, right?

884
00:34:10,291 --> 00:34:12,375
- Well, that depends,
I guess.

885
00:34:12,458 --> 00:34:15,958
I mean, it isn't like I want
to do rash or reckless things.

886
00:34:17,458 --> 00:34:18,791
- Go with grace.

887
00:34:18,875 --> 00:34:21,333
May the blessing of the spirits
be with you.

888
00:34:21,416 --> 00:34:22,333
- [grunts]

889
00:34:22,416 --> 00:34:23,791
What's that mean?

890
00:34:23,875 --> 00:34:25,625
- It's a good luck prayer.

891
00:34:25,708 --> 00:34:29,166
It means come back safe,
so you better.

892
00:34:29,250 --> 00:34:30,375
- Thanks, Emilia.

893
00:34:30,458 --> 00:34:31,625
I'll do my best.

894
00:34:33,583 --> 00:34:36,875
Okay, I'm off.
- Take care.

895
00:34:41,791 --> 00:34:44,750
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

896
00:34:44,833 --> 00:34:48,375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

897
00:34:48,458 --> 00:34:50,666
- [gasps]
- [gasps]

898
00:34:51,125 --> 00:34:52,250
Has something happened?

899
00:34:52,333 --> 00:34:53,791
- Yeah, it's awful.

900
00:34:53,875 --> 00:34:56,291
Several of the village children
have suddenly gone missing.

901
00:34:56,375 --> 00:34:58,583
Now everybody is out looking
all over for them.

902
00:34:58,666 --> 00:35:00,375
- Was I too late?

903
00:35:02,958 --> 00:35:05,375
Wait, don't tell me they're--
[grunts]

904
00:35:05,458 --> 00:35:06,000
- What is it?

905
00:35:06,083 --> 00:35:08,916
- [panting]

906
00:35:11,083 --> 00:35:15,458
- [panting]

907
00:35:20,541 --> 00:35:22,833
- The barrier's been broken.
- [gasps]

908
00:35:22,916 --> 00:35:25,583
When something like that's
been disturbed, what happens?

909
00:35:25,666 --> 00:35:27,333
- Mabeasts can cross
the boundary

910
00:35:27,416 --> 00:35:29,416
and enter the village.
- Mabeasts?

911
00:35:29,500 --> 00:35:31,083
- They're known
as unholy creatures

912
00:35:31,166 --> 00:35:32,375
of the Witch's creation.

913
00:35:32,458 --> 00:35:34,583
Enemies of humanity
that have magic powers.

914
00:35:34,666 --> 00:35:36,875
Within the forest,
they live wild

915
00:35:36,958 --> 00:35:37,958
and in great number.

916
00:35:38,041 --> 00:35:39,375
- Whoa, hang on a sec.

917
00:35:39,458 --> 00:35:42,000
Are you trying to tell me tons
more dogs like that one

918
00:35:42,083 --> 00:35:43,333
are out there?

919
00:35:43,416 --> 00:35:44,625
[grunts]

920
00:35:46,416 --> 00:35:48,541
It looks like the kids are out
in the forest.

921
00:35:48,625 --> 00:35:50,250
Get some help.
Tell everyone.

922
00:35:50,333 --> 00:35:51,958
- [grunts]
Right.

923
00:35:53,291 --> 00:35:54,541
- [grunts]

924
00:35:54,625 --> 00:35:55,958
- [gasps]
Wait, what is it

925
00:35:56,041 --> 00:35:57,791
you're going to--
- I have to go out there

926
00:35:57,875 --> 00:35:59,833
and rescue those kids.
- Hold on.

927
00:35:59,916 --> 00:36:02,291
You can't make that decision
on your own.

928
00:36:02,375 --> 00:36:04,500
With Lord Roswaal away
from home,

929
00:36:04,583 --> 00:36:07,375
can you be certain this isn't
just a ruse to divert

930
00:36:07,458 --> 00:36:08,750
our attention away
from the mansion?

931
00:36:08,833 --> 00:36:11,208
- No, but what do you think
we should do about this?

932
00:36:11,291 --> 00:36:13,500
Ignore the poor kids who are
in trouble right now,

933
00:36:13,583 --> 00:36:15,375
go back to the mansion,
and tighten security?

934
00:36:15,458 --> 00:36:17,416
If it's not gonna bother you
that all the villagers might

935
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:18,583
wind up dead tomorrow,

936
00:36:18,666 --> 00:36:19,833
then I guess that's
a solid option.

937
00:36:19,916 --> 00:36:21,416
- [gasps]

938
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:22,875
- You know I'm right, Rem.

939
00:36:22,958 --> 00:36:26,000
We're the only ones who are able
to do something about this.

940
00:36:26,083 --> 00:36:28,166
- But why go so far?

941
00:36:28,250 --> 00:36:31,208
What is it about this village
that matters so much to you?

942
00:36:31,291 --> 00:36:32,583
- You remember Petra?

943
00:36:32,666 --> 00:36:34,041
Someday when she's all grown up,

944
00:36:34,125 --> 00:36:36,333
she wants to move to the capitol
and make clothes.

945
00:36:36,416 --> 00:36:37,916
- Huh?
- Lucas wants to prove himself

946
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:41,375
and eventually be the village's
best woodcutter like his dad.

947
00:36:41,458 --> 00:36:42,958
Milda wants to take some
of the prettiest flowers

948
00:36:43,041 --> 00:36:45,041
growing in the field,

949
00:36:45,125 --> 00:36:46,041
craft them into
a beautiful crown,

950
00:36:46,125 --> 00:36:47,500
and give it to his mother.

951
00:36:47,583 --> 00:36:49,875
Meina's excited because it won't
be long before she'll have

952
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:51,458
a little baby sister.

953
00:36:51,541 --> 00:36:54,041
And the brothers Dyne and Cain
are always fighting over which

954
00:36:54,125 --> 00:36:56,500
one of them will be lucky enough
to marry Petra.

955
00:37:00,875 --> 00:37:02,833
All of those kids matter to me.

956
00:37:02,916 --> 00:37:04,083
I know their names.

957
00:37:04,166 --> 00:37:05,458
I know their faces.

958
00:37:05,541 --> 00:37:08,250
And I know what they each want
to do in the future.

959
00:37:08,333 --> 00:37:10,125
On top of that,
I promised them

960
00:37:10,208 --> 00:37:12,375
we'd do radio calisthenics
again tomorrow.

961
00:37:13,708 --> 00:37:16,791
I keep my promises and I
make sure others keep theirs.

962
00:37:17,583 --> 00:37:18,916
No matter what happens,

963
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:22,000
I'm gonna do those exercises
with those kids again.

964
00:37:22,083 --> 00:37:24,750
That means I'm going in there.

965
00:37:28,458 --> 00:37:30,291
- Very well, then.
- [grunts]

966
00:37:30,375 --> 00:37:32,833
- I was given orders to keep
an eye on you.

967
00:37:32,916 --> 00:37:35,041
It wouldn't be right
if I failed to do so.

968
00:37:35,125 --> 00:37:37,041
- Yeah, absolutely.

969
00:37:37,125 --> 00:37:38,166
After all, you need
to be there to make sure

970
00:37:38,250 --> 00:37:40,666
I don't do anything shady.

971
00:37:42,625 --> 00:37:43,750
- Right.

972
00:37:44,833 --> 00:37:46,000
- [grunts]

973
00:37:46,083 --> 00:37:47,458
[chain rattling]

974
00:37:48,583 --> 00:37:50,958
Um, Rem-Rim,
is that a--

975
00:37:51,041 --> 00:37:53,416
- It's for protection.
- But it seems so--

976
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:54,875
- It's for protection.
- [grunts]

977
00:38:00,875 --> 00:38:02,625
- [grunting]

978
00:38:03,916 --> 00:38:05,083
- [grunts]

979
00:38:05,166 --> 00:38:06,416
[sniffing]

980
00:38:06,500 --> 00:38:07,166
We're getting closer.

981
00:38:07,250 --> 00:38:08,875
I smell living creatures.

982
00:38:08,958 --> 00:38:10,166
- Is it the kids?

983
00:38:10,250 --> 00:38:12,333
- I'm not certain but
it doesn't smell like

984
00:38:12,416 --> 00:38:13,458
beasts to me.

985
00:38:25,583 --> 00:38:26,750
- Look, up ahead.
It's them!

986
00:38:26,833 --> 00:38:28,583
[breathing heavily]

987
00:38:28,666 --> 00:38:29,791
[grunts]

988
00:38:29,875 --> 00:38:31,375
- [exhales]
- She's breathing.

989
00:38:31,458 --> 00:38:32,750
They're still alive.

990
00:38:32,833 --> 00:38:34,958
- That's true,
but their breathing is shallow.

991
00:38:35,041 --> 00:38:36,500
They're all unconscious
and weak.

992
00:38:36,583 --> 00:38:39,083
If left alone--
- They're weak?

993
00:38:39,166 --> 00:38:40,375
Is it the curse?

994
00:38:42,791 --> 00:38:44,833
And we finally found them.

995
00:38:44,916 --> 00:38:46,750
Rem, can't you do anything
to reverse it?

996
00:38:46,833 --> 00:38:48,708
- Not a spell of this magnitude.

997
00:38:48,791 --> 00:38:50,291
If only my sister were with us.

998
00:38:50,375 --> 00:38:52,000
I'm sure she could do something.

999
00:38:52,083 --> 00:38:53,541
I'll try what I can

1000
00:38:53,625 --> 00:38:54,875
and cast a healing spell
to comfort them.

1001
00:38:54,958 --> 00:38:57,708
When they're calm we can carry
them back with us.

1002
00:38:59,541 --> 00:39:01,833
- Yeah, sounds good.
And I'll--

1003
00:39:01,916 --> 00:39:04,416
Who am I kidding?
I'm so useless.

1004
00:39:04,500 --> 00:39:07,041
I'll keep an eye out for--
- Subaru.

1005
00:39:07,125 --> 00:39:08,791
- Petra, you're awake.

1006
00:39:08,875 --> 00:39:10,125
All right, good.

1007
00:39:10,208 --> 00:39:11,541
You're a tough girl.

1008
00:39:11,625 --> 00:39:12,958
I need you to save
your strength, though.

1009
00:39:13,041 --> 00:39:14,500
Don't overdo it.

1010
00:39:14,583 --> 00:39:15,875
I'll take you back home where
you can say good-bye

1011
00:39:15,958 --> 00:39:17,333
to the pain.
Just rest up

1012
00:39:17,416 --> 00:39:19,041
for the time being--
- One is--

1013
00:39:19,125 --> 00:39:22,958
one is still in--in the--

1014
00:39:23,041 --> 00:39:24,708
- Hold on.
What did you say?

1015
00:39:24,791 --> 00:39:27,041
Petra!
[grunts]

1016
00:39:28,916 --> 00:39:30,333
Damn it, she's right.

1017
00:39:30,416 --> 00:39:32,583
I don't see the little girl
with the braid anywhere.

1018
00:39:32,666 --> 00:39:34,125
- No, please don't go.

1019
00:39:34,208 --> 00:39:35,458
It's far too dangerous.

1020
00:39:35,541 --> 00:39:37,750
And if the mabeast took her
it may already be--

1021
00:39:37,833 --> 00:39:40,125
- Look, I understand what
you're trying to tell me,

1022
00:39:40,208 --> 00:39:42,875
I really do,
but you heard what Petra said.

1023
00:39:42,958 --> 00:39:45,791
She was trying to tell us
the other girl was taken away.

1024
00:39:46,666 --> 00:39:47,791
Even in her state,

1025
00:39:47,875 --> 00:39:49,583
she showed concern
for her missing friend

1026
00:39:49,666 --> 00:39:51,750
before asking for my help.
Don't you see?

1027
00:39:51,833 --> 00:39:54,625
She put her friend's life
and well-being before her own.

1028
00:39:56,541 --> 00:39:58,750
I want to respect
Petra's feelings.

1029
00:39:58,833 --> 00:40:00,291
If you take something on,

1030
00:40:00,375 --> 00:40:02,083
you should see it through
to the bitter end.

1031
00:40:02,166 --> 00:40:03,458
- If you get too greedy,

1032
00:40:03,541 --> 00:40:05,000
then you run the risk
of taking on

1033
00:40:05,083 --> 00:40:07,708
much more than you could ever
possibly carry back with you.

1034
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:10,958
- I know but that's the reason
you came along, isn't it?

1035
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:12,833
- And what does the situation
have to do with me?

1036
00:40:12,916 --> 00:40:16,666
- Those kids need you now more
than they ever did before.

1037
00:40:16,750 --> 00:40:18,083
When the villagers show up here,

1038
00:40:18,166 --> 00:40:20,083
leave the children with them
and then follow me out

1039
00:40:20,166 --> 00:40:22,041
into the forest.
[grunts]

1040
00:40:22,125 --> 00:40:24,333
- We don't know the threat
our opponent presents

1041
00:40:24,416 --> 00:40:25,958
or when the villagers
will arrive.

1042
00:40:26,041 --> 00:40:28,541
At worst there's always a chance
that you'll wander off somewhere

1043
00:40:28,625 --> 00:40:30,291
and I would never be able
to find you.

1044
00:40:30,375 --> 00:40:32,583
- It'll be fine 'cause
I'm confident that you won't

1045
00:40:32,666 --> 00:40:35,291
lose track of me.
- What makes you so sure?

1046
00:40:35,375 --> 00:40:37,000
- Even if no one else does,

1047
00:40:37,083 --> 00:40:38,791
I know that you
can pick up my scent.

1048
00:40:39,750 --> 00:40:42,750
The foul odor that hangs on me.

1049
00:40:42,833 --> 00:40:44,125
The Witch's scent.

1050
00:40:44,208 --> 00:40:45,500
Isn't that right?

1051
00:40:45,583 --> 00:40:46,583
- [gasps]
Wait, Subaru.

1052
00:40:46,666 --> 00:40:49,500
How do you know about--
- No idea.

1053
00:40:49,583 --> 00:40:50,750
[chuckles]
There's a ton

1054
00:40:50,833 --> 00:40:52,166
I don't understand.

1055
00:40:52,250 --> 00:40:54,833
So much that no matter how
many times I start over,

1056
00:40:54,916 --> 00:40:57,375
I can't seem to find
the answer I'm looking for.

1057
00:40:59,333 --> 00:41:02,250
Just like there are many things
you want to ask me,

1058
00:41:02,333 --> 00:41:05,541
there are a ton of things that
I want to ask you about, too.

1059
00:41:05,625 --> 00:41:07,083
So when all of this
is taken care of,

1060
00:41:07,166 --> 00:41:08,291
we should talk.

1061
00:41:08,375 --> 00:41:10,208
We can chat until our voices
are hoarse.

1062
00:41:10,291 --> 00:41:11,791
It's a promise.

1063
00:41:11,875 --> 00:41:13,416
- Huh?

1064
00:41:14,583 --> 00:41:17,125
- I just want you to know
I trust you, Rem.

1065
00:41:17,208 --> 00:41:18,500
And this is my attempt
at showing

1066
00:41:18,583 --> 00:41:20,125
that you can trust me also.

1067
00:41:20,208 --> 00:41:21,250
So that promise I made,

1068
00:41:21,333 --> 00:41:23,708
I'm sticking to it.

1069
00:41:24,791 --> 00:41:26,083
- All right, very well.

1070
00:41:26,166 --> 00:41:28,541
Then I promise on my end, too.

1071
00:41:28,625 --> 00:41:30,666
I plan on asking you
many questions

1072
00:41:30,750 --> 00:41:32,083
so be ready for them.
- You got it.

1073
00:41:32,166 --> 00:41:35,125
- And once the villagers arrive
to help the children,

1074
00:41:35,208 --> 00:41:37,583
I'll join you.
Just be careful out there.

1075
00:41:37,666 --> 00:41:39,083
Don't do anything reckless.

1076
00:41:39,166 --> 00:41:41,500
- Appreciate the concern,
but don't worry about a thing.

1077
00:41:41,583 --> 00:41:43,666
I'm demonically
inspired tonight.

1078
00:41:43,750 --> 00:41:44,833
- Demonically inspired?

1079
00:41:44,916 --> 00:41:47,791
- Demon version
of divine inspiration.

1080
00:41:47,875 --> 00:41:50,666
For some reason
it's my favorite phrase lately.

1081
00:41:50,750 --> 00:41:53,083
- Please take care.
I'll join you soon.

1082
00:41:59,333 --> 00:42:01,541
- If the one who cursed
those kids from the village

1083
00:42:01,625 --> 00:42:03,875
really turns out to be that dog
from earlier today,

1084
00:42:03,958 --> 00:42:07,041
then there's no way I can lose
this fight, right?

1085
00:42:07,333 --> 00:42:08,416
[grunts]

1086
00:42:08,500 --> 00:42:10,291
I can smell beasts.

1087
00:42:17,166 --> 00:42:18,958
[gasps]

1088
00:42:21,750 --> 00:42:22,916
Is it a trap?

1089
00:42:26,416 --> 00:42:28,958
Emilia wouldn't hesitate
to save her.

1090
00:42:34,875 --> 00:42:38,375
- [whimpers]

1091
00:42:38,458 --> 00:42:40,500
- Thank goodness she's alive.
